REQUIRED BLOG LINK LOGIC
1. Detect locale first.
2. Use backlink text exactly:
   Hash Hedge Blog
3. Use backlink target:
   - en: https://hashhedge.com/blog
   - ru: https://hashhedge.com/blog/ru
   - pt: https://hashhedge.com/blog/pt
   - kz: https://hashhedge.com/blog/kz
   - other locale: https://hashhedge.com/blog/<locale_code>

REQUIRED BACKLINK BLOCK
Use exactly:
<div class="article-backlink" onclick="window.location.href='__BLOG_URL__'">
  <div class="article-backlink-arrow">←</div>
  <div class="article-backlink-text">Hash Hedge Blog</div>
</div>

REQUIRED LAYOUT WRAPPING
1. Inside .t-container wrap the full article flow in:
   <div class="article-content"> ... </div>
2. .article-content must stretch to full available width.
3. Do NOT apply max-width: 760px to article-content.
4. Content blocks must use the full available width.

HOOK GENERATION RULES
1. The hook above the title must ALWAYS be one continuous hook phrase.
2. It must feel like one short sentence-like thematic line.
3. It must NEVER be taxonomy or breadcrumbs.
4. It must NEVER contain separators like:
   · / | , and category pairings
5. Forbidden example:
   СЫРЬЕВЫЕ АКТИВЫ · ПРОП-ТРЕЙДИНГ
6. Good examples:
   КАК ТОРГОВАТЬ СЕРЕБРО КАК ПРОП-ТРЕЙДЕР
   ЧТО НУЖНО ЗНАТЬ О ТОРГОВЛЕ XAG/USDT
7. If no natural hook exists in the document, generate one in the detected language.

LINK RULES
1. Detect links and linked phrases in the source article when present.
2. Render every inline article link with:
   <span class="article-link" onclick="window.location.href='URL_HERE'">linked text</span>
3. If the source contains a textual reference to another article/page with a known URL, render it as a clickable yellow inline brand link.
4. All inline links must be yellow and hover subtly.

QUOTE DETECTION RULES
1. Detect if a paragraph is a true quote, testimonial, cited speech, dialogue line, or clearly framed quoted statement.
2. Quote formatting is allowed only when at least one of these is true:
   - the text is explicitly enclosed in quotation marks
   - the source labels it as a quote/testimonial/citation
   - the paragraph is clearly attributed speech
3. Do NOT convert ordinary emphasis, tips, observations, or advisory lines into quote blocks.
4. A standalone sentence that is not explicitly quoted must remain .t-descr.
5. Render true quotes using:
   <div class="article-quote">
     <div class="article-quote-line"></div>
     <div class="article-quote-text">...</div>
   </div>
6. The quote line must be yellow.
7. The quote must have larger spacing than normal paragraphs.
8. The line height must naturally follow content height. Do NOT use min-height.

CONTENT ORDER RULE
Use exactly this order:
backlink
hook
title
meta
hero
table of contents
intro/body start
mid-article banner
remaining body
faq accordion
final promo block

TABLE OF CONTENTS RULES
1. Always generate a block after hero and before the first article paragraph.
2. Use:
   <div class="article-toc-item" onclick="document.getElementById('section-1').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'})">...</div>
3. Each TOC item must point to a matching section wrapper ID.
4. Each main article section must have an id like:
   <div class="article-section" id="section-1">
5. On hover TOC items must turn yellow.
6. Localize the TOC title based on detected document language.

MID-ARTICLE BANNER RULES
1. A banner is mandatory in every article.
2. Place it approximately in the middle of the article, or at the most natural contextual break.
3. Banner text is NOT taken from DOCX. Generate it automatically.
4. Banner text must be semantically connected to the article topic.
5. Do NOT use URL-based logo rendering.
6. Do NOT use background-image for the logo.
7. Use this exact inline SVG inside .article-banner-logo:
