8. Banner button text must be localized.
9. Banner button onclick:
   window.location.href='https://www.hashhedge.com/client/login?redirect=/challenge'
10. Banner should feel like a premium prop-firm sales element.

FAQ ACCORDION RULES
1. FAQ must be an accordion list.
2. Only one item may be open at a time.
3. The first item may be open by default.
4. Closed state icon: +
5. Open state icon: −
6. Use:
   <div class="faq-toggle-icon">+</div>
7. The script must replace the icon content:
   - open => −
   - closed => +
8. Icon must be large and semi-transparent by default.
9. On hover icon becomes yellow.
10. Add a <script> that closes all other FAQ items before opening the clicked one.

FINAL PROMO BLOCK RULES
1. Before the end of the article, add a visually strong promo block.
2. It must use a gold border.
3. Remove the yellow divider line entirely.
4. The final action must be a real button, not plain text.
5. Use:
   <div class="article-final-promo">
     <div class="article-final-promo-title">...</div>
     <div class="article-final-promo-descr">...</div>
     <div class="article-final-promo-button" onclick="window.location.href='https://www.hashhedge.com/client/login?redirect=/challenge'">...</div>
   </div>
6. Final promo text and button text must be localized.
7. Final promo text must be automatically generated and relevant to the article topic and product.

CONTENT RULES
1. Extract title from DOCX.
2. Generate a short continuous hook phrase if missing.
3. Hook phrase must not be breadcrumb-like and must not use separator dots.
4. Meta must always be:
   {reading_time} | {today_date}
5. Today's date must always be current date.
6. Localize the reading-time phrase and other generated labels.
7. All body text uses .t-descr unless the content is a true quote block.
8. All headings use .t-title or .article-section-title.
9. Bold text in descriptions must keep body color and only change weight.

SEO RULES
1. The title must include the main article keyword naturally.
2. The hook phrase should reinforce the main topic naturally.
3. The first 2–3 paragraphs must clearly explain the topic using natural search language.
4. Section titles must be descriptive and keyword-relevant.
5. FAQ questions must be phrased like realistic search questions when appropriate.
6. Banner text and final promo text must also be relevant to the article keyword cluster and product context.
7. The article must stay readable and helpful, not spammy.

IMAGE PLACEHOLDER + ALT TEXT RULES
1. Always add hero placeholder after meta.
2. Above hero placeholder add:
   <!-- HERO_IMAGE_URL: insert image url here -->
   <!-- HERO_IMAGE_ALT: concise descriptive alt text in the detected language -->
3. Then:
   <div class="article-hero">HERO IMAGE</div>

4. Add inline placeholders:
   - 1 if article below 1000 words
   - 2 if article 1000 words or more

5. Above each inline placeholder add:
   <!-- INLINE_IMAGE_URL: insert image url here -->
   <!-- INLINE_IMAGE_ALT: concise descriptive alt text in the detected language -->

6. Then:
   <div class="article-inline-image">INLINE IMAGE</div>

7. ALT text must be specific to the article topic and image context.
8. ALT text must be descriptive, concise, and SEO-relevant.

SCRIPT RULE
Add a script function named toggleFaq(el) that:
- finds all .faq-item elements
- removes faq-item-open from all items except the clicked one
- updates every .faq-toggle-icon text
- open item icon => −
- all closed item icons => +
- toggles faq-item-open on the clicked item

FINAL RULE
Return only the final ready-to-paste HTML block.
